I really need to organize my stuff and rethink some things, before I continue to research my ancestors. To get started I decided to create a Challenge and hope some of you can use it too.  
It's a little wild, so I probably forgot one or two Tasks.  


&nbsp;


If the Challenge isn't for you but you're interested in Genealogy: Check out the [Ancestors, Heritage and Genealogy](https://habitica.com/groups/guild/658b25b0-daec-451b-b945-7e093cbed262)-Guild


&nbsp;


I'll close the Challenge around End of May / Beginning of June

On your way to climbing Mount TBR, you decide to take a less trodden path. To your feet, hidden beneath the well-known volumes that have been there since the beginning, you see a whole new crest. Slowly you realize that it is the crest you have been seeing from the distance, but avoided for unknown reasons. After taking a closer look, you recognize it as the Crest of Borrowed Books. How did it get so big? How much time has gone by since anyone tried to climb it? You're not sure how safe it is to get up there, but you're intrigued and decide to take a closer look.

&nbsp;

This challenge is designed to focus on the books in your TBR pile that aren't actually yours: If you're like me, your friends know you love books and sometimes give you one they think you'd appreciate. Or you mention that a certain book sounds interesting and next thing you know, it is on top of your TBR pile. Or you have library books over library books you somehow don't get to. Participate in this challenge and make an extra-effort to return those books back to their homes.

&nbsp;

The winner will be chosen by RNG of all participants who have checked the "Destination reached!" task. The challenge will run untill May 9th.

&nbsp;

PS: If you don't know it yet (which i really doubt), check out @shanaqui's ["Climbing Mt. To Be Read"](https://habitica.com/challenges/6182b93c-bec4-403a-8c6b-4f39f19beb26) challenge!
